definition.value: a hypomagnesemia AE that  requires <0.9 - 0.7 mg/dL; <0.4 - 0.3 mmol/L
a hypomagnesemia AE that  requires <0.7 mg/dL; <0.3 mmol/L; life-threatening consequences
a hypophosphatemia AE that requires <LLN - 2.5 mg/dL; <LLN - 0.8 mmol/L
a hypophosphatemia AE that requires <2.5 - 2.0 mg/dL; <0.8 - 0.6 mmol/L
a hypophosphatemia AE that requires <2.0 - 1.0 mg/dL; <0.6 - 0.3 mmol/L
a hypophosphatemia AE that requires <1.0 mg/dL; <0.3 mmol/L; life-threatening consequences
a cough AE that shows an increased rate of coughing
a viral infection AE that is caused by a herpes virus. Note that there are 8 herpesvirus types.
a herpez zoster AE that occurs in children.
a nervous system AE that shows abnormal neurologic reflexes, which can be tesetd by the knee jerk reaction.

an abnormal reflex AE where the patient has a condition of below normal or absent reflexes (areflexia). Hyporeflexia is the condition of below normal or absent reflexes. Hyporeflexia is generally associated with a lower motor neuron deficit (at the alpha motor neurons from the spinal cord to muscle).

an abnormal reflex AE that has an outcome of overactive reflexes, indicative of upper motor neuron disease as well as lessening or loss of control ordinarily exerted by higher brain centers of lower neural pathways.
a cardiac arrest AE where there is no discernible electrical activity on the ECG monitor.

Asystole is the absence of electrical activity in the heart, as evidenced by a flat line on an EKG. Cardiac arrest is a more general term for conditions where the heart is not circulating blood. Ventricular fibrillation (V-fib) or pulseless Ventricular tachycardia (V-tach) are examples of EKG rhythms which also will produce cardiac arrest, but are not asystole. Pulseless electrical activity (PEA) is another catch-all where there is an otherwise survivable EKG, but no blood is circulating. This can be caused by trauma to the heart, or tremendous blood loss, among other reasons. See: https://answers.yahoo.com/question/index?qid=20081027100243AAy0yt4
an eye inflammation AE that occurs at the corneal area.
an infection AE where one or two eyes get infected by bacteria, fungi, or viruses.
an inflammation AE that shows inflammation at the location of appendix.

label.value: electrocardiogram QT corrected interval prolonged AE

definition.value: an electrocardiogram QT prolonged AE that estimates the QT interval at a heart rate of 60 bpm.
an anorexia AE that has loss of appetite of greasy food.
a coordination and balance disorder AE that has difficulty in standing
a skin AE that has an outcome of injury to the skin and underlying tissues from exposure to a large external dose of radiation
a gastric disorder AE that shows an rupture in the stomach
an injury AE that refers to break or burst suddenly (esp. of a pipe, a vessel, or a bodily part such as an organ or membrane)
a radiation skin injury AE that shows skin burn from exposure to a large external dose of radiation
a troponin AE which indicates increased levels of cardiac troponin I in a biological specimen
a musculoskeletal or connective tissue AE that has greater growth than expected for age.
a surgery AE that has the finding of a previously undocumented problem that occurs after a thoracic procedure.
a uterine AE that has a rupture in the uterine wall.
a female reproductive system AE that has the finding of rupture of the fallopian tube wall.

an endocrine system AE that occurs when the adrenal cortex does not produce enough of the hormone cortisol and in some cases, the hormone aldosterone. It may be due to a disorder of the adrenal cortex as in Addison's disease or primary adrenal insufficiency.

an endocrine system AE that has signs and symptoms that resemble Cushing's disease or syndrome: buffalo hump obesity, striations, adiposity, hypertension, diabetes, and osteoporosis, usually due to exogenous corticosteroids.
an endocrine system AE that has unusually late sexual maturity.
an endocrine system AE that has an increase in production of parathyroid hormone by the parathyroid glands. This results in hypercalcemia (abnormally high levels of calcium in the blood).
an endocrine system AE that has a decrease in production of parathyroid hormone by the parathyroid glands.
an endocrine system AE that has inappropriate masculinization occurring in a female or prepubertal male.
an endocrine system AE that has unusually early development of secondary sexual features; the onset of sexual maturation begins usually before age 8 for girls and before age 9 for boys.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of tumor-like collection of serum in the tissues.
a medical intervention site AE that has a circumscribed, inflammatory and necrotic erosive lesion on the jejunal mucosal surface close to the anastomosis site following a gastroenterostomy procedure.
a medical intervention site AE that has a finding of blood leakage from the intestinal stoma.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of leakage due to breakdown of a pancreatic anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of leakage of bile due to breakdown of a biliary anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of blockage of the normal flow of the contents of the intestinal stoma.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of leakage of contents from an intestinal stoma (surgically created opening on the surface of the body).
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of a previously undocumented problem related to the vascular access site.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of leakage due to breakdown of a pharyngeal anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of protrusion of the intestinal stoma (surgically created opening on the surface of the body) above the abdominal surface.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of bleeding from the urostomy site.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of blood leakage from the tracheostomy site.
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of leakage due to breakdown of a fallopian tube anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
a medical intervention site AE that has the finding of leakage of urine due to breakdown of a bladder anastomosis (surgical connection of two separate anatomic structures).
